// Supersonic Ball HP
// For the HP Prime
// Version 1.01
// Remake of original TI-83 Plus & TI-84 Plus game
// (c) 2013-22 Dream of Omnimaga
// https://djomnimaga.music-2000.com/
initialize();
fadeIn();
fadeOut();
titleScreen();
mainGame();
LOCAL levelData, currentLevel, score, levelListOffset;
LOCAL highScore, tileSet, tileSetWindow, motionBlur;
LOCAL escPressed, cachedMode, numSeparateSetting;
LOCAL hardwareRevision, gameSpeed, screenshotMode, screenshotModeWait;

EXPORT ssball()
BEGIN
  IF POS(HVars,"sSBallHighScore") == 0 THEN
    HVars("sSBallHighScore") := 0;
  END;
  screenshotMode := 1;
  tileSet := 6;
  motionBlur := 256;
  escPressed := 0;
  //The last screen before starting the game
  DIMGROB_P(G1,320,240);
  BLIT_P(G1,G0);
  WHILE escPressed=0 DO
    initialize();
    fadeOut();
    titleScreen();
    fadeOut();
    IF escPressed=0 THEN
      mainGame();
    END;
  END;
  HSeparator := numSeparateSetting;
  BLIT_P(G3,G1);
  fadeIn();
  DIMGROB_P(G1,1,1);
  DIMGROB_P(G2,1,1);
  DIMGROB_P(G3,1,1);
  DIMGROB_P(G4,1,1);
  DIMGROB_P(G5,1,1);
  DIMGROB_P(G6,1,1);
  DIMGROB_P(G7,1,1);
  DIMGROB_P(G8,1,1);
  DIMGROB_P(G9,1,1);
END;

mainGame()
BEGIN
  LOCAL ballAniFrm=0, ballAniDelay=0, canJump=0, doIHaveToFadeIn=0;
  LOCAL forVar1=0, forVar2=0, forVar3=0;
  LOCAL randTop=0, randBottom=0, lvlRandomizerA=0, lvlRandomizerB=0;
  LOCAL tempVar1=0, drawWallX=0, drawWallY1=0, drawWallY2=0;
  LOCAL ballXPosition=0, ballYPosition=0, ballXSpeed=0, ballYSpeed=0, enterPressed=0;
  LOCAL xPosAdjusted=0, yPosAdjusted=0, canMove=0;
  LOCAL bgAutoScrollAmount=0, blinkingTimer=0, tileAnimFrame, tileSpdControl;
  //data necessary to generate random levels, current level, how many time game was played through and remaining time
  LOCAL levelData={0}, currentLevel, completeLvlCycle=1, timeLeft := 1, timeCycle := 0;
  //score and the data for the current level layout
  LOCAL platformColumns={0};
  // List containing level data and setup of other variables
  //            YSTRT,RNDINTRV,SLOPE,MINHEIGHT,MAXHEIGHT,TIME,WALLSPR1,2,3,4,BGSPR1,2,3,4,WALLANIMSPD,PARALSCROLLSPD
  levelData := {124,5,5,4,5,89,3,4,5,6,7,7,7,7,2,4,
                18,16,4,5,16,90,2,2,2,2,19,19,19,19,20,2,
                100,1,8,4,5,90,15,15,15,15,21,21,21,21,20,3,
                70,4,4,5,8,60,23,24,25,26,19,19,20,20,2,3,
                74,50,50,5,50,28,15,15,15,15,1,1,1,1,20,1,
                100,8,2,5,9,90,11,12,13,12,12,13,12,11,7,2,
                100,8,2,4,5,140,9,9,9,9,8,8,8,8,20,2,
                124,1,3,4,5,90,0,0,0,0,16,16,16,16,20,8,
                100,1,4,5,6,70,1,1,1,1,22,22,22,22,20,3,
                6,2,2,5,6,100,6,5,4,3,30,31,32,33,1,2,
                6,2,1,4,8,300,34,34,34,34,17,18,17,18,15,4,
                100,3,1,4,13,200,27,27,27,27,10,10,10,10,1,3,
                124,1,1,4,5,90,24,8,24,8,2,2,2,2,1,2,
                120,1,1,5,6,135,2,2,14,14,7,7,14,14,10,2,
                6,50,1,5,5,300,9,9,9,9,16,16,16,16,20,8,
                6,10,1,5,5,666,14,14,14,16,14,14,14,14,1,2,
                120,1,1,5,50,150,28,29,28,29,24,24,24,24,4,4,
                6,5,1,4,5,150,7,7,7,7,9,9,9,9,20,4,
                50,1,1,5,10,100,21,22,21,22,8,8,8,8,1,8,
                50,2,2,5,7,69,19,19,20,20,29,29,29,29,20,4,
                56,50,50,5,20,18,20,13,14,21,1,10,6,5,2,2};
  score := 0;
  BLIT_P(G9,0,0,96,1248,"spriteData",0,0,48,624);
  BLIT_P(G9,96,0,192,1248,"spriteData2",0,0,24,312);
  BLIT_P(G9,192,0,256,1248,"spriteData3",0,0,64,1248);
  //Loop through all 16 levels until time runs out.
  WHILE timeLeft>0 DO
    currentLevel := 1;
    WHILE timeLeft>0 AND currentLevel<21 DO
      doIHaveToFadeIn := 1;
      //WHICH LV-1*17
      levelListOffset := (currentLevel-1)*16+1;
      FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 16 DO
        platformColumns[forVar1] := 0;
        platformColumns[forVar1+355] := 0;
      END;
      platformColumns[17] := levelData[levelListOffset];
      platformColumns[372] := levelData[levelListOffset]+1;
      platformColumns[373] := levelData[levelListOffset]+2;
      platformColumns[374] := levelData[levelListOffset]+3;
      platformColumns[18] := levelData[levelListOffset]-1;
      platformColumns[19] := levelData[levelListOffset]-2;
      //RANDOMIZE
      lvlRandomizerA := 1;
      lvlRandomizerB := 5;
      FOR forVar1 FROM 20 TO 340 DO
        lvlRandomizerA := lvlRandomizerA - 1;
        IF lvlRandomizerA<1 THEN
          lvlRandomizerA := levelData[levelListOffset+1];
          randTop := iPart(4*RANDOM()-2);
          randBottom := iPart(4*RANDOM()-2);
        END;
        platformColumns[forVar1] := platformColumns[forVar1-1];
        platformColumns[forVar1+355] := platformColumns[forVar1+354];
        lvlRandomizerB := lvlRandomizerB - 1;
        IF lvlRandomizerB<1 THEN
          lvlRandomizerB := levelData[levelListOffset+2];
          platformColumns[forVar1] := platformColumns[forVar1]+randTop;
          IF platformColumns[forVar1]<5 THEN
            platformColumns[forVar1] := 5;
          END;
          platformColumns[forVar1+355] := platformColumns[forVar1+355]+randBottom;
          IF platformColumns[forVar1+355]<(platformColumns[forVar1]+levelData[levelListOffset+3]) THEN
            platformColumns[forVar1+355] := platformColumns[forVar1]+levelData[levelListOffset+3];
          END;
          IF platformColumns[forVar1+355]>(platformColumns[forVar1]+levelData[levelListOffset+4]) THEN
            platformColumns[forVar1+355] := platformColumns[forVar1]+levelData[levelListOffset+4];
          END;
          IF platformColumns[forVar1]>(128-levelData[levelListOffset+3]) THEN
            platformColumns[forVar1] := 128-levelData[levelListOffset+3];
          END;
          If platformColumns[forVar1+355]>128 THEN
            platformColumns[forVar1+355] := 128;
          END;
        END;
      END;
      FOR forVar1 FROM 341 TO 354 DO
        platformColumns[forVar1] := platformColumns[340];
        platformColumns[forVar1+355] := platformColumns[695];
      END;
      // Generate each level background frame;
      FOR forVar3 FROM 0 TO 3 DO
        FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 256 STEP 32 DO
          FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 352 STEP 32 DO
            BLIT_P(G5,forVar1,forVar2+(272*forVar3),forVar1+32,forVar2+32+(272*forVar3),G9,tileSet*32,levelData[levelListOffset+10+forVar3]*32,32+(tileSet*32),levelData[levelListOffset+10+forVar3]*32+32);
          END;
        END;
      END;
      ballXPosition := 220;
      ballYPosition := (platformColumns[17]-3)*16;
      canJump := 0;
      ballAniFrm := 0;
      canMove := 2;
      ballAniDelay := 4;
      tileAnimFrame := 1;
      tileSpdControl := 1;
      timeLeft := IP(timeLeft+(levelData[levelListOffset+5]/completeLvlCycle));
      IF timeLeft<35 THEN
        timeLeft := 35;
      END;
      IF timeLeft>999 THEN
        timeLeft := 999;
      END;
      timeCycle := 15;
      WHILE ballXPosition>132 AND ballXPosition<5426 AND timeLeft>0 DO
        //Code specific to level 3, 9 and 15 (auto-scrolling background)
        bgAutoScrollAmount := bgAutoScrollAmount-(4*(currentLevel=3))+(4*(currentLevel=9))+(8*(currentLevel=15));
        IF bgAutoScrollAmount>31 THEN
          bgAutoScrollAmount := bgAutoScrollAmount-32;
        END;
        IF bgAutoScrollAmount<1 THEN
          bgAutoScrollAmount := bgAutoScrollAmount+32;
        END;
        xPosAdjusted := IP((ballXPosition/levelData[levelListOffset+15]) MOD 16);
        yPosAdjusted := IP((ballYPosition/levelData[levelListOffset+15]) MOD 16);
        RECT_P(G7,32,32,352,272,#800080);
        RECT_P(G2,100,40,220,200,#800080);
        //Tiles/bg animation control
        tileSpdControl := tileSpdControl-1;
        IF tileSpdControl<1 THEN
          tileSpdControl := levelData[levelListOffset+14]*(1+(hardwareRevision>1));
          tileAnimFrame := tileAnimFrame-1;
          IF tileAnimFrame<1 THEN
            tileAnimFrame := 4;
          END;
        END;
        //Copy background to buffer
        BLIT_P(G3,0,0,320,240,G5,(2*xPosAdjusted)+bgAutoScrollAmount,(2*yPosAdjusted)+(272*tileAnimFrame)-272,(2*xPosAdjusted)+320+bgAutoScrollAmount,(2*yPosAdjusted)+240+(272*tileAnimFrame)-272);
        yPosAdjusted := IP((ballXPosition-1)/16);
        xPosAdjusted := IP((ballXPosition-1) MOD 16);
        //draw the tunnel
        tempVar1 := levelData[levelListOffset+5+tileAnimFrame]*32;
        FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 10 DO
          drawWallX := forVar1*16-xPosAdjusted+16;
          drawWallY1 := platformColumns[forVar1+yPosAdjusted+2]*16-ballYPosition;
          drawWallY2 := platformColumns[forVar1+yPosAdjusted+357]*16-ballYPosition;
          IF ((drawWallY1+16)*2)>0 THEN
            IF forVar1>2 AND forVar1<8 THEN
              RECT_P(G2,(drawWallX)*2,(drawWallY1-16)*2,(drawWallX+16)*2,(drawWallY1+32)*2,#000000);
            END;            
            BLIT_P(G7,(drawWallX)*2,(drawWallY1+16)*2,(drawWallX+16)*2,(drawWallY1+32)*2,G9,tileSet*32,tempVar1,32+(tileSet*32),tempVar1+32,#800080);
          END;
          IF ((drawWallY2+32)*2)<304 THEN
            IF forVar1>2 AND forVar1<8 THEN
              RECT_P(G2,(drawWallX)*2,(drawWallY2+16)*2,(drawWallX+16)*2,(drawWallY2+64)*2,#000000);
            END;
            BLIT_P(G7,(drawWallX)*2,(drawWallY2+16)*2,(drawWallX+16)*2,(drawWallY2+32)*2,G9,tileSet*32,tempVar1,32+(tileSet*32),tempVar1+32,#800080);
          END;
        END;
        //The timer goes down 
        timeCycle := timeCycle-1;
        IF timeCycle<1 THEN
          timeCycle := 30;
          timeLeft := timeLeft - 1;
        END;
        //After clearing a LV the timer blinks for a while. This also controls the ball spinning animation.
        ballAniFrm := ballAniFrm-(ballXSpeed/4);
        IF ballAniFrm>4 THEN
          ballAniFrm := ballAniFrm-3.99;
        END;
        IF ballAniFrm<0 THEN
          ballAniFrm := ballAniFrm+3.99;
        END;
        IF blinkingTimer>0 THEN
          blinkingTimer := blinkingTimer-1;
        END;
        //The original game checks for directional keypress every 6 loop iteration.
        canMove := canMove-1;
        IF canMove<1 THEN
          canMove := 6;
          IF ballYSpeed<2 THEN
            ballYSpeed := ballYSpeed+(1/(1+(hardwareRevision>1)));
          END;
          ballXSpeed := ballXSpeed-(ISKEYDOWN(7)/(1+(hardwareRevision>1)))+(ISKEYDOWN(8)/(1+(hardwareRevision>1)));
        END;
        IF ballXSpeed=5 THEN
          ballXSpeed := 4;
        END;
        IF ballXSpeed=-5 THEN
          ballXSpeed := -4;
        END;
        IF ballYSpeed=5 THEN
          ballYSpeed := 4;
        END;
        IF ballXSpeed≠0 and GETPIX_P(G2,202,159)≠#800080 THEN
          ballXSpeed := -ballXSpeed;
          ballXPosition := ballXPosition-5;
        END;
        IF ballXSpeed≠0 and GETPIX_P(G2,182,159)≠#800080 THEN
          ballXSpeed := -ballXSpeed;
          ballXPosition := ballXPosition+5;
        END;
        ballXPosition := ballXPosition+(2*ballXSpeed);
        IF ballYSpeed≠0 and GETPIX_P(G2,192,169)≠#800080 THEN
          ballYSpeed := -ballYSpeed/1.25;
          ballYPosition := ballYPosition-5;
        END;
        IF ballYSpeed≠0 and GETPIX_P(G2,192,149)≠#800080 THEN
          ballYSpeed := -ballYSpeed;
          ballYPosition := ballYPosition+5;
        END;
        ballYPosition := ballYPosition+(2*ballYSpeed);
        IF canJump=0 THEN
          IF ISKEYDOWN(30)=1 AND GETPIX_P(G2,192,176)≠#800080 AND ballYSpeed>-1 THEN
            canJump := 1;
            ballYSpeed := ballYSpeed+2;
            IF ballYSpeed>5 THEN
              ballYSpeed := 4;
            END;
          END;
        END;
        IF ISKEYDOWN(30)=0 THEN
          canJump := 0;
        END;
        //Draw the ball
        BLIT_P(G7,176,144,208,176,G9,tileSet*32,(32*IP(ballAniFrm))+1120,32+(tileSet*32),(32*IP(ballAniFrm))+1152,#800080);
        //The blocks
        BLIT_P(G3,0,0,320,240,G7,32,32,352,272,#800080);
        //HUD frame
        RECT_P(G3,2,0,317,2,tileSetWindow[tileSet+17],tileSetWindow[tileSet+25]);
        RECT_P(G3,2,27,317,29,tileSetWindow[tileSet+17],tileSetWindow[tileSet+25]);
        RECT_P(G3,0,2,2,27,tileSetWindow[tileSet+17],tileSetWindow[tileSet+25]);
        RECT_P(G3,317,2,319,27,tileSetWindow[tileSet+17],tileSetWindow[tileSet+25]);
        FILLPOLY_P(G3,{{2,2},{317,2},{317,27},{2,27}}, tileSetWindow[tileSet+33], 128);
        //Shows the timer (no zoom)
        IF ballAniFrm=0 or blinkingTimer=0 THEN
          BLIT_P(G3,1,0,57,23,G6,115,17,171,40,#2A2C26);
          FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 2 STEP 2 DO
            FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 2 STEP 2 DO
              TEXTOUT_P(timeLeft,G3,forVar2+60,forVar1,6,tileSetWindow[tileSet+1]);
            END;
          END;
          TEXTOUT_P(timeLeft,G3,61,1,6,tileSetWindow[tileSet+9]);
        END;
        //Shows the level number (no zoom)
        BLIT_P(G3,106,0,134,23,G6,174,17,202,40,#2A2C26);
        tempVar1 := currentLevel+(completeLvlCycle*20)-20;
        FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 2 STEP 2 DO
          FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 2 STEP 2 DO
            TEXTOUT_P(tempVar1,G3,forVar2+136,forVar1,6,tileSetWindow[tileSet+1]);
          END;
        END;
        TEXTOUT_P(tempVar1,G3,137,1,6,tileSetWindow[tileSet+9]);
        //And then the score (no zoom)
        BLIT_P(G3,180,0,216,23,G6,205,17,241,40,#2A2C26);
        tempVar1 := score;
        FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 2 STEP 2 DO
          FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 2 STEP 2 DO
            TEXTOUT_P(tempVar1,G3,forVar2+221,forVar1,6,tileSetWindow[tileSet+1]);
          END;
        END;
        TEXTOUT_P(tempVar1,G3,222,1,6,tileSetWindow[tileSet+9]);
        //Paste everything on screen! 
        IF doIHaveToFadeIn=1 THEN
          fadeIn();
          doIHaveToFadeIn := 0;
        ELSE
          BLIT_P(G0,0,0,320,240,G3,0,0,320,240,#2A2C26,motionBlur);
          IF hardwareRevision=3 THEN
            screenshotModeWait := .029*screenshotMode;
            WAIT(screenshotModeWait/2);
          END;
        END;
        //Exits the game (by triggering Game Over)
        IF ISKEYDOWN(4)=1 THEN
          currentLevel := 20;
          timeLeft := 0;
        END;
      END;
      score := score+timeLeft;
      currentLevel := currentLevel+1;
      blinkingTimer := 10;
      IF timeLeft>0 THEN
        fadeOut();
      END;
    END;
    completeLvlCycle := completeLvlCycle+1;
  END;
  //Game over
  RECT_P(G3,107,110,216,112,tileSetWindow[tileSet+17],tileSetWindow[tileSet+25]);
  RECT_P(G3,107,137,216,139,tileSetWindow[tileSet+17],tileSetWindow[tileSet+25]);
  RECT_P(G3,105,112,107,137,tileSetWindow[tileSet+17],tileSetWindow[tileSet+25]);
  RECT_P(G3,216,112,218,137,tileSetWindow[tileSet+17],tileSetWindow[tileSet+25]);
  FILLPOLY_P(G3,{{107,112},{216,112},{216,137},{107,137}}, tileSetWindow[tileSet+33], 128);
  BLIT_P(G3,110,110,214,133,G6,246,17,350,40,#2A2C26);
  IF score > HVars("sSBallHighScore") THEN
    BLIT_P(G3,120,47,172,64,G6,258,0,310,17,#2A2C26);
    HVars("sSBallHighScore") := score;  
    FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 2 STEP 2 DO
      FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 2 STEP 2 DO
        TEXTOUT_P(HVars("sSBallHighScore"),G3,forVar2+175,forVar1+47,1,#FF0000);
      END;
    END;
  TEXTOUT_P(HVars("sSBallHighScore"),G3,176,48,1,#FFFF00);
  END;
  BLIT_P(G0,0,0,320,240,G3,0,0,320,240,#2A2C26);
  WHILE ISKEYDOWN(30)=0 DO
  END;
END;

titleScreen()
BEGIN
  LOCAL forVar1=0, forVar2=0, aniCounter=0;
  LOCAL ballAniFrm=0, themeKeyPressed=0;
  LOCAL colHeight=0, heightChg=0, heightChgDir=.12, bgOffset=0;
  LOCAL enterPressed=0;
  BLIT_P(G9,0,0,48,624,"spriteData",0,0,48,624);
  BLIT_P(G9,48,0,96,624,"spriteData2",0,0,24,312);
  BLIT_P(G9,96,0,128,624,"spriteData3",0,0,64,1248);

  WHILE enterPressed=0 and escPressed=0 DO
    // Generate title background;
    FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 240 STEP 16 DO
      FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 320 STEP 16 DO
        BLIT_P(G5,forVar1,forVar2,forVar1+16,forVar2+16,G9,0+(tileSet*16),160,16+(tileSet*16),176);
      END;
    END;
    // Generate the spinning balls on title screen;
    FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 14 DO
      FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 3 DO
        BLIT_P(G5,16*forVar2+336,16*forVar1,16*forVar2+352,16*forVar1+16,G9,tileSet*16,16*forVar2+560,16+(tileSet*16),16*forVar2+576);
      END;
    END;
    //text with black outline rendering and small title logos around big wavy one.
    FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 3 DO
      FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 3 DO
        IF forVar1=0 AND (forVar2=0 or forVar2=2) THEN
          BLIT_P(G6,64*forVar2,40,64*forVar2+126,55,"titleLogo",0,tileSet*15,63,(tileSet*15)+15,RGB(128,0,128));
        END;
        TEXTOUT_P("  ©2022 Dream of Omnimaga www.discord.gg/cuZcfcF    Highscore:",G6,forVar2,forVar1,1,tileSetWindow[tileSet+1]);
        TEXTOUT_P("Press Enter   Time: LV: PTS: Game Over",G6,forVar2,17+forVar1,6,tileSetWindow[tileSet+1]);
      END;
    END;
    TEXTOUT_P("  ©2022 Dream of Omnimaga www.discord.gg/cuZcfcF    Highscore:",G6,1,1,1,tileSetWindow[tileSet+9]);
    TEXTOUT_P("Press Enter   Time: LV: PTS: Game Over",G6,1,18,6,tileSetWindow[tileSet+9]);
    // Main title loop;
    WHILE (themeKeyPressed>0 OR (ISKEYDOWN(7)=0 AND ISKEYDOWN(8)=0)) AND escPressed=0 AND enterPressed=0 DO
      themeKeyPressed := themeKeyPressed-1;
      //The background
      BLIT_P(G3,0,0,320,240,G5,bgOffset,bgOffset,320+bgOffset,240+bgOffset);
      //Wavy logo effect
      FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 62 STEP 1 DO
        heightChg := heightChgDir*3+heightChg;
        IF heightChg>1.1 OR heightChg<-1.11 THEN
          heightChgDir := -heightChgDir;
        END;
        colHeight := colHeight+heightChg;
        BLIT_P(G3,33+(forVar1*4),27-colHeight,37+(forVar1*4),115+colHeight,"titleLogo",forVar1,tileSet*15,forVar1+1,(tileSet*15)+15,RGB(128,0,128));
        //On the virtual calc this slows the game down for smoother animated capture that you can speed back up using your favorite image or video editor
        IF ISKEYDOWN(15) and hardwareRevision=3 THEN
          screenshotMode := 10;
          INVERT_P();
          WAIT(.5);
          INVERT_P();
        END;
        //Enable/Disable TI-83+/84+ monochrome screen motion blur effect
        IF ISKEYDOWN(42) THEN
          motionBlur := 256;
        END;
        IF ISKEYDOWN(43) THEN
          motionBlur := 150;
        END;
        //Starts the game
        IF ISKEYDOWN(30) THEN
          enterPressed := 1;
        END;
        IF ISKEYDOWN(4) THEN
          escPressed := 1;
        END;
      END;
      //Scrolling looping background calculation
      bgOffset := bgOffset+(gameSpeed[hardwareRevision+6]);
      IF bgOffset>15 THEN
        bgOffset := bgOffset - 16;
      END;
      //spinning balls on each side
      FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 1 DO
        BLIT_P(G3,304*forVar2,0,304*forVar2+16,240,G5,(16*ballAniFrm)+336,0,(16*ballAniFrm)+352,240,RGB(128,0,128));
      END;
      //Copy text to buffer
      BLIT_P(G3,33,225,291,242,G6,0,0,258,17,#2A2C26);
      BLIT_P(G3,120,144,172,161,G6,258,0,310,17,#2A2C26);
      FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 2 STEP 2 DO
        FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 2 STEP 2 DO
          TEXTOUT_P(HVars("sSBallHighScore"),G3,forVar2+175,forVar1+144,1,tileSetWindow[tileSet+1]);
        END;
      END;
      TEXTOUT_P(HVars("sSBallHighScore"),G3,176,145,1,tileSetWindow[tileSet+9]);
      IF ballAniFrm>1 THEN
        BLIT_P(G3,108,162,218,185,G6,0,17,110,40,#2A2C26);
      END;
      //Version number
      FOR forVar2 FROM 0 TO 1 DO
        TEXTOUT_P("Version v1.01",G3,128+forVar2,132,1,#000000);
      END;
      //Same for the small logo strips
      BLIT_P(G3,32,5,288,20,G6,0,40,256,55,#2A2C26);
      BLIT_P(G3,32,115,288,130,G6,0,40,256,55,#2A2C26);
      IF aniCounter=0 THEN
        fadeIn();
      ELSE
        BLIT_P(G0,G3,0,0,320,240,#2A2C26,motionBlur);
        IF hardwareRevision=3 THEN
          screenshotModeWait := .014*screenshotMode;
          WAIT(screenshotModeWait);
        END;
      END;
      aniCounter := aniCounter+1;
      IF aniCounter=gameSpeed[hardwareRevision+3] THEN
        aniCounter := 1;
        ballAniFrm := ballAniFrm+1;
        IF ballAniFrm>3 THEN
          ballAniFrm := 0;
        END;
      END;
    END;
    tileSet := tileSet-ISKEYDOWN(7)+ISKEYDOWN(8);
    IF ISKEYDOWN(7) OR ISKEYDOWN(8) THEN
      themeKeyPressed := 8;
    END;
    IF tileSet=8 THEN
      tileSet := 0;
    END;
    IF tileSet=-1 THEN
      tileSet := 7;
    END;
  END;
END;

fadeIn()
BEGIN
  LOCAL forVar1=0;
  BLIT_P(G4,G3);
  FOR forVar1 FROM 16 DOWNTO gameSpeed[hardwareRevision] STEP gameSpeed[hardwareRevision] DO
    BLIT_P(G3,0,0,320/forVar1,240/forVar1,G4,0,0,320,240);
    FILLPOLY_P(G3,{{0,0},{320,0},{320,240},{0,240}}, #000000, 256-(16*forVar1));
    BLIT_P(G0,0,0,320,240,G3,0,0,320/forVar1,240/forVar1,#AA66FF,motionBlur);
    IF hardwareRevision=3 THEN
      screenshotModeWait := .01*screenshotMode;
      WAIT(screenshotModeWait);
    END;
  END;
END;

fadeOut()
BEGIN
  LOCAL forVar1=0;
  BLIT_P(G4,G0);
  FOR forVar1 FROM gameSpeed[hardwareRevision] TO 16 STEP gameSpeed[hardwareRevision] DO
    BLIT_P(G3,0,0,320/forVar1,240/forVar1,G4,0,0,320,240);
    FILLPOLY_P(G3,{{0,0},{320,0},{320,240},{0,240}}, #000000, 256-(16*forVar1));
    BLIT_P(G0,0,0,320,240,G3,0,0,320/forVar1,240/forVar1,#AA66FF,motionBlur);
    IF hardwareRevision=3 THEN
      screenshotModeWait := .01*screenshotMode;
      WAIT(screenshotModeWait);
    END;
  END;
END;

initialize()
BEGIN
  LOCAL ticksOne=0, ticksTwo=0, tickDifference=0, forVar1=0;
  escPressed := 0;
  numSeparateSetting := HSeparator;
  HSeparator := 3;
  //Checks hardware revision using speed check
  ticksOne:=TICKS;
  FOR forVar1 FROM 0 TO 9999 DO
  END;
  ticksTwo:=TICKS;
  // returns the number of seconds between 2 TICKS
  tickDifference := (ticksTwo-ticksOne)/1000;
  hardwareRevision := 1;
  IF tickDifference < 0.015 THEN
    hardwareRevision:= 3;
  END;
  IF tickDifference > .035 AND tickDifference < .09 THEN
    hardwareRevision := 2;
  END;
  //fade in, ball animation speed on title screen, background offset on title screen
  gameSpeed := {1, .4, .4, 3, 7, 7, 2, 1, 1, 0, 0};
  //list containing the colors of the text window. 1:TEXTBORDER 2:TEXT 3:OUTERBORDER 4:INNERBORDER 5: WINDOW
  tileSetWindow := {#000039, #000000, #1A1C16, #000039, #000000, #1A1C16, #000039, #000099,
                    #FFFFFF, #FFFFFF, #C0C7B6, #FFFFFF, #FFFFFF, #C0C7B6, #FFFFFF, #00FF00,
                    #FFFFFF, #FFFFFF, #1A1C16, #FFFFFF, #FFFFFF, #9EAB88, #FFFFFF, #FFFF00,
                    #000039, #000000, #9EAB88, #FFFFFF, #FFFFFF, #9EAB88, #000039, #000099,
                    #000099, #666666, #1A1C16, #000099, #666666, #1A1C16, #000099, #99004C};
  // SPRITE DATA IS LOCATED AT THE VERY BOTTOM OF THIS FILE.
  //Collision stuff
  DIMGROB_P(G2,320,240);
  // Temporary screen and background storages. G3 is where everything usually end up before being copied to the screen;
  DIMGROB_P(G3,320,240);
  // This one is for fade-in/out routines and is also used to store the background during gameplay
  DIMGROB_P(G4,320,240);
  // This one is for background stuff such as tiled backdrops and title screen spinning balls on each side.
  DIMGROB_P(G5,414,1088,#FF00FF);
  // This one is for text and small logos that can be pre-rendered.
  DIMGROB_P(G6,393,55,#2A2C26);
  // This one is for the collision detection
  DIMGROB_P(G7,400,320);
  DIMGROB_P(G8,320,240);
  //Sprites cache (zoom pre-render)
  DIMGROB_P(G9,256,1248);
END;
